WEBVTT

00:07.674 --> 00:09.443
VANESSA: <i>Previously on</i> Penny Dreadful...

00:09.543 --> 00:11.978
I was introduced to a
woman who saved my life.

00:12.078 --> 00:13.313
A mental doctor.

00:13.414 --> 00:14.981
Good afternoon. May I help you?

00:15.081 --> 00:16.650
I'm here to see Dr. Seward.

00:16.750 --> 00:17.718
Take a seat, Miss Ives.

00:17.818 --> 00:19.720
There are no emotions
unwelcome in this room,

00:19.820 --> 00:21.354
and if this process
doesn't appeal to you,

00:21.455 --> 00:22.456
the door is there.

00:23.657 --> 00:25.291
(GRUNTING)

00:26.660 --> 00:28.962
<i>My name is Kaetenay.</i>

00:29.062 --> 00:30.797
- You must come with me.
- Where?

00:30.897 --> 00:33.333
KAETENAY: <i>America. Our son needs us.</i>

00:38.004 --> 00:39.039
- (GUNFIRE)
- (GROANS)

00:39.840 --> 00:41.174
Welcome home, Ethan.

00:42.409 --> 00:43.376
ETHAN: <i>Who are you?</i>

00:43.477 --> 00:44.645
MAN: We're your liberators.

00:44.745 --> 00:46.112
From those Federals who
would have hung you

00:46.212 --> 00:47.414
from the neck until dead.

00:47.514 --> 00:48.815
You work for my father.

00:48.915 --> 00:50.316
Man wants to see you again.

00:50.417 --> 00:51.985
DR. SWEET: <i>Dr. Alexander Sweet.</i>

00:52.085 --> 00:53.687
Director of Zoological Studies.

00:53.787 --> 00:54.988
Noah in his ark.

00:55.088 --> 00:56.890
VANESSA: <i>Do you have a favorite?</i>

00:56.990 --> 00:58.158
DR. SWEET: <i>The unloved ones.</i>

00:58.258 --> 01:00.494
All the broken and shunned creatures.

01:00.594 --> 01:01.695
Someone's got to care for them.

01:01.795 --> 01:03.530
Who shall it be, if not us?

01:03.630 --> 01:05.699
- (KNOCKING)
- Dr. Jekyll.

01:05.799 --> 01:06.967
Dr. Frankenstein.

01:07.067 --> 01:09.235
- I have conquered death.
- The old work?

01:09.335 --> 01:10.871
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

01:10.971 --> 01:12.473
FRANKENSTEIN: I've created monsters.

01:12.573 --> 01:15.141
Soon, he will kneel to us.

01:15.241 --> 01:18.211
This sad little world is ours.

01:18.311 --> 01:19.480
FRANKENSTEIN: You must
help me destroy her.

01:19.580 --> 01:21.047
What if I could tame her?

01:22.082 --> 01:23.817
(GASPING IN TERROR)

01:23.917 --> 01:26.987
(THE MASTER WHISPERING)
Tell me about Vanessa Ives.

01:27.087 --> 01:29.322
I don't know anything!
I don't know anything!

01:29.423 --> 01:32.459
THE MASTER: <i>You will
open</i> her secrets to me.

01:33.059 --> 01:36.129
My name is Dracula.

01:38.231 --> 01:40.601
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS
IN MULTIPLE LANGUAGES)

01:42.000 --> 01:48.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:13.299 --> 02:14.501
(SCOFFS)

02:25.211 --> 02:26.580
(DOOR OPENS)

02:27.548 --> 02:29.049
(DOOR CREAKING)

02:32.553 --> 02:35.355
You are aware, sir, of the extremity.

02:35.456 --> 02:36.490
Yes.

02:36.590 --> 02:38.792
I mean, sir, the illegality.

02:39.960 --> 02:42.463
I mean, sir, we butcher 'em.

02:43.329 --> 02:45.599
I believe that's what I'm paying for.

02:48.969 --> 02:51.972
Well, I hope you have a
memorable evening, sir.

02:52.072 --> 02:53.474
I'm sure of it.

03:26.507 --> 03:28.041
(GASPING)

03:37.017 --> 03:38.419
(GASPING)

03:50.964 --> 03:52.298
(GRUNTS)

04:14.120 --> 04:15.722
(GRUNTING)

04:17.991 --> 04:18.992
MAN: Please! No!

04:22.062 --> 04:23.730
- (CHOKING)
- (GUN CLICKS)

04:30.404 --> 04:31.805
(EXHALES)

04:45.151 --> 04:46.787
Now...

04:48.188 --> 04:50.424
You are mine.

04:51.758 --> 04:53.760
<i>â™ª</i>

04:56.508 --> 05:00.250
- sync and correctins by Caio -
- www.addic7ed.com -

06:36.129 --> 06:37.831
(INDISTINCT MUTTERING)

06:59.019 --> 07:00.120
Bury 'em.

07:08.995 --> 07:10.431
RUSK: <i>Then where else would they go?</i>

07:11.164 --> 07:12.332
There's nothing else out there.

07:12.433 --> 07:13.767
I'm a bit more concerned with that

07:13.867 --> 07:16.236
fucking trainload of dead bodies.

07:16.336 --> 07:17.504
Now, if you'll excuse me,

07:17.604 --> 07:18.672
- I have to...
- (DOOR OPENING)

07:20.173 --> 07:22.042
Where's my goddamn prisoner?

07:22.843 --> 07:24.210
Ask him.

07:24.310 --> 07:26.680
You Rusk? And you are?

07:27.147 --> 07:29.450
Federal Marshal Franklin Ostow.

07:29.550 --> 07:30.551
What happened?

07:30.651 --> 07:32.953
He was taken from the train by brigands.

07:33.920 --> 07:35.321
Your duty is discharged.

07:35.422 --> 07:37.157
I'll sign the extradition order.

07:37.257 --> 07:38.825
- Go home.
- RUSK: No, sir.

07:39.426 --> 07:42.596
My duties will be discharged
when I see Ethan Talbot

07:42.696 --> 07:44.831
at the end of a rope and not before.

07:44.931 --> 07:45.899
If you're telling...

07:45.999 --> 07:47.300
There'll be no conversation about it.

07:48.835 --> 07:50.437
This is a federal matter now.

07:50.537 --> 07:52.673
My duty is to the Queen.

07:54.207 --> 07:56.176
So I see it as an imperial matter,

07:56.276 --> 07:58.779
which rather trumps your
territorial jurisdiction.

07:58.879 --> 08:00.581
If you so choose,

08:00.681 --> 08:02.783
take it up with the British
Ambassador in Washington.

08:02.883 --> 08:07.454
In the meantime, I intend to bring Mr.
Talbot to heel,

08:07.554 --> 08:09.189
at which point... (EXHALES)

08:10.356 --> 08:11.792
I will deliver him to the appropriate

08:11.892 --> 08:13.627
representatives of your government.

08:15.429 --> 08:17.764
And how you gonna do that, Inspector?

08:17.864 --> 08:19.299
You familiar with the territory?

08:21.001 --> 08:22.202
No, sir.

08:23.537 --> 08:24.938
But I have been on horseback

08:25.038 --> 08:26.773
for long stretches of
my military career.

08:26.873 --> 08:28.975
I've learned how to hunt, track,

08:29.075 --> 08:30.444
and shoot from the saddle.

08:31.912 --> 08:33.346
It's no great matter to me.

08:34.515 --> 08:36.450
One-armed British man's
gonna go into that desert

08:36.549 --> 08:38.018
and do some tracking, is he?

08:39.152 --> 08:40.621
There's no tracking required.

08:41.655 --> 08:43.188
I know precisely where he is.

08:43.289 --> 08:46.527
They're heading for a
town noted as Cascabel.

08:46.627 --> 08:47.794
I shall apprehend him there.

08:47.894 --> 08:49.129
And how do you know that?

08:49.996 --> 08:51.264
All to the west of the desert.

08:52.433 --> 08:54.200
That area in pink on the map.

08:55.135 --> 08:56.369
What does it say?

08:58.939 --> 09:00.474
(OSTOW) Talbot Range.

09:04.578 --> 09:06.880
The wolf is returning to his den.

09:09.315 --> 09:11.785
(OSTOW) All right, I'll get the men.

09:11.885 --> 09:14.120
We'll get saddled up
and head to Cascabel.

09:38.512 --> 09:39.513
(SIGHING)

09:40.213 --> 09:41.715
(DOOR CREAKING)

09:47.921 --> 09:49.456
(RENFIELD CHUCKLES SOFTLY)
Hello, Miss Ives.

09:50.090 --> 09:51.725
Oh, do sit down.

09:51.825 --> 09:54.160
The doctor is just finishing
up with another patient.

09:54.260 --> 09:55.562
Thank you.

10:02.436 --> 10:04.304
RENFIELD: When you've
completed your session

10:04.405 --> 10:07.273
I'll need you to fill
out some documentation.

10:07.373 --> 10:09.242
Basic information:

10:09.342 --> 10:11.111
address and the like, you know.

10:12.446 --> 10:13.880
Medical history.

10:13.980 --> 10:15.348
Of course.

10:18.151 --> 10:19.886
I'm glad the bells have stopped.

10:21.154 --> 10:24.024
For Tennyson. (CHUCKLES)
Made my head hurt.

10:24.124 --> 10:25.426
My head hurt.

10:35.068 --> 10:36.169
(DOOR OPENS)

10:44.377 --> 10:45.712
This way, please.

10:48.649 --> 10:49.850
(DOOR OPENS)

10:58.725 --> 11:00.060
Gloves are a nice touch.

11:01.528 --> 11:02.963
Didn't want to scratch my hand.

11:03.063 --> 11:05.599
You mean you didn't want me to
see you scratching your hand.

11:05.699 --> 11:09.470
The gloves are to remind you
but the itch is still there.

11:09.570 --> 11:10.571
Sit down.

11:12.739 --> 11:15.308
I record my sessions for later review,

11:15.409 --> 11:16.710
saves taking notes.

11:19.212 --> 11:20.380
I've never heard my own voice.

11:20.481 --> 11:22.849
You wouldn't like it. No one does.

11:23.950 --> 11:25.619
These are for my ears only.

11:27.220 --> 11:28.922
It makes you uneasy. Why?

11:29.990 --> 11:32.759
An actual record of our
deeds through life,

11:32.859 --> 11:34.795
and permanent.

11:35.762 --> 11:37.564
How can we forget anything?

11:37.664 --> 11:39.733
Why would you want to?

11:39.833 --> 11:42.235
Who wants to remember their shame?

11:42.335 --> 11:44.805
Or sin? Or... or foolishness?

11:46.339 --> 11:47.708
Let's start with sin.

11:48.509 --> 11:49.976
(WHIRRING)

11:50.544 --> 11:51.778
Have you sinned?

11:52.813 --> 11:54.247
Everyone has sinned.

11:54.347 --> 11:55.381
- Have they?
- Mmm-hmm.

11:55.482 --> 11:57.418
Including you? Yes.

11:57.518 --> 11:59.219
- When?
- (SCOFFS)

11:59.953 --> 12:01.422
How long is your cylinder?

12:03.223 --> 12:04.891
Start with the first time.

12:08.228 --> 12:10.564
(SIGHS) Apart from...

12:10.664 --> 12:12.633
childhood indiscretions,

12:12.733 --> 12:14.435
the first of importance then.

12:15.769 --> 12:16.970
I...

12:18.238 --> 12:19.706
I betrayed my dearest friend Mina

12:19.806 --> 12:21.608
on the eve of her wedding.

12:21.708 --> 12:22.909
How?

12:25.245 --> 12:26.312
How?

12:27.781 --> 12:29.382
I seduced her fiance.

12:30.383 --> 12:31.618
DR. SEWARD: What was the result?

12:33.654 --> 12:35.221
It led to catastrophe.

12:36.923 --> 12:38.692
And eventually her death.

12:38.792 --> 12:40.727
You blame yourself for her death.

12:41.995 --> 12:43.263
Indirectly.

12:43.363 --> 12:44.731
- What directly then?
- (WHIRRING)

12:44.831 --> 12:46.667
It's hard to say. Can you turn that off?

12:48.802 --> 12:49.970
No.

12:53.139 --> 12:54.641
Tell me your story.

12:56.443 --> 12:58.144
And if it involves murder?

12:58.945 --> 13:00.280
Then let it.

13:01.014 --> 13:02.382
And much beyond that.

13:03.784 --> 13:05.118
What's beyond murder?

13:22.836 --> 13:24.638
If you credit my story...

13:25.539 --> 13:27.373
if you believe the things I tell you,

13:28.542 --> 13:30.477
you'll never sleep quietly again.

13:31.244 --> 13:32.779
Not as you did before.

13:35.015 --> 13:36.417
Can you believe?

13:40.721 --> 13:41.855
Tell me.

13:50.531 --> 13:52.499
FRANKENSTEIN: I think
you're just morbid.

13:53.299 --> 13:54.801
DR. JEKYLL: Practical.

13:54.901 --> 13:56.036
I swear my father has suffered

13:56.136 --> 13:58.071
every ailment an overstuffed
Briton can endure,

13:58.171 --> 14:00.173
from gout to dropsy.

14:00.273 --> 14:02.042
But he can't last forever.

14:02.142 --> 14:03.510
And then?

14:03.610 --> 14:06.680
Then I get the title and the
estates and a proper lab.

14:06.780 --> 14:08.214
Off to Harley Street I go.

14:08.314 --> 14:10.617
Oh, yes, you'll fit in very well there.

14:15.456 --> 14:16.490
I meant your work.

14:16.590 --> 14:18.091
You meant my complexion.

14:19.560 --> 14:22.529
Cambridge to Harley Street.
Makes no bloody difference.

14:22.629 --> 14:24.297
Once a wog, always a wog.

14:24.397 --> 14:25.499
Henry.

14:26.833 --> 14:28.334
My mother died, you know.

14:29.836 --> 14:31.772
After my noble pater left India.

14:32.439 --> 14:35.175
Abandoned his exotic whore
to her own devices.

14:37.043 --> 14:39.045
But she was tainted by then.

14:39.145 --> 14:40.981
Rejected by her own family.

14:42.416 --> 14:43.684
Untouchable.

14:44.918 --> 14:46.319
Do you know how she died?

14:47.488 --> 14:48.889
Leprosy.

14:51.692 --> 14:52.893
(SCOFFS)

14:53.894 --> 14:56.396
Oh, there's poetry in
that, don't you think?

14:56.497 --> 14:58.699
Truly untouchable.

14:59.199 --> 15:00.200
I'm sorry.

15:00.300 --> 15:01.968
And you wonder why I wait
for that man to die.

15:02.068 --> 15:03.570
It's not for the money or the title.

15:03.670 --> 15:05.739
It's for the justice of the thing.

15:07.073 --> 15:09.576
Of that duality that
makes us who we are,

15:09.676 --> 15:11.044
he is wholly evil.

15:12.479 --> 15:13.480
Duality?

15:13.580 --> 15:16.349
We are all two things
in a way, are we not?

15:16.450 --> 15:18.251
Deep in the marrow.

15:18.351 --> 15:20.487
Angel and Devil. Light and dark.

15:21.488 --> 15:22.789
The pull between the two

15:22.889 --> 15:25.459
is the active verb which
energizes our lives.

15:29.395 --> 15:31.231
Or so I've come to believe, anyway.

15:31.331 --> 15:32.899
Thus my current work.

15:35.268 --> 15:36.537
Really, Victor, you must eat.

15:37.370 --> 15:38.371
Get your strength back.

15:38.472 --> 15:39.506
It's chops and spuds

15:39.606 --> 15:41.307
for breakfast every day now, old man.

15:41.408 --> 15:42.676
As you say, Doctor.

15:45.979 --> 15:47.448
And the injections?

15:48.982 --> 15:50.884
We'll have a care to that, won't we?

15:51.585 --> 15:52.953
You know I'll help in any way I can.

15:53.053 --> 15:54.788
Yes, thank you, Henry.

15:58.258 --> 16:01.428
Now, you were intending
to take me to your lab.

16:01.528 --> 16:03.564
Oh, yes, my lab.

16:04.898 --> 16:06.266
It's right over there.

16:07.333 --> 16:08.569
I work at Bedlam.

16:18.011 --> 16:20.414
DR. JEKYLL: I was lucky
to get the job at all.

16:20.514 --> 16:21.615
As you can imagine, the more

16:21.715 --> 16:23.750
reputable hospitals and
academies weren't lining up

16:23.850 --> 16:26.086
to hire the uppity little half-breed.

16:26.186 --> 16:27.721
What's your actual position here?

16:27.821 --> 16:29.189
I'm the resident somnolist.

16:29.289 --> 16:31.191
Meaning, I keep the most
violent patients sedated

16:31.291 --> 16:33.560
until the Crown can decide how
to best dispense with them,

16:34.461 --> 16:36.162
which is mostly to let them rot,

16:36.262 --> 16:38.965
or to more actively starve
them in some cases.

16:39.733 --> 16:43.203
But they do give me a lab and
no end of diverting subjects.

16:43.303 --> 16:44.738
(DISTANT SCREAMING)

16:46.507 --> 16:48.374
We're subterranean now,

16:48.475 --> 16:50.511
coiling away in the bowels of the city.

16:50.611 --> 16:52.245
They keep the worst of them down here.

16:52.345 --> 16:54.481
The cannibals and the infanticides.

16:54.581 --> 16:56.249
The criminally insane.

16:56.349 --> 16:59.152
The angel seeks the light,
the beast seeks the dark.

17:00.587 --> 17:02.055
Oh, they never see the light.

17:02.155 --> 17:03.424
They only see me.

17:06.859 --> 17:08.194
(DOOR CLANGS)

17:08.294 --> 17:09.796
(CREAKING)

17:14.701 --> 17:16.301
(LIQUID BUBBLING)

17:23.108 --> 17:24.144
(DOOR CLOSING)

17:24.243 --> 17:25.512
(LOCKING DOOR)

17:38.792 --> 17:40.326
FRANKENSTEIN: A barber's chair?

17:41.127 --> 17:42.696
With my own modifications.

17:43.497 --> 17:45.532
I need to look into their eyes, you see.

17:45.632 --> 17:47.367
Mirrors to the soul.

17:48.402 --> 17:49.403
(EXHALES)

17:49.503 --> 17:50.637
What?

17:51.672 --> 17:53.073
Lily.

17:53.173 --> 17:54.441
Yes?

17:54.941 --> 17:56.643
I'll have to bring her here?

17:58.645 --> 17:59.946
Into this awful place.

18:00.046 --> 18:02.315
Yes. When we're ready.

18:02.416 --> 18:03.550
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

18:05.185 --> 18:06.820
So much I've put her through.

18:08.689 --> 18:10.090
Her life has been...

18:13.126 --> 18:14.561
I stopped her breath when she was Brona

18:14.661 --> 18:16.062
and gave it back to her as Lily.

18:18.832 --> 18:20.667
And now I do this to her.

18:21.234 --> 18:24.137
What we won't do for love.

18:40.454 --> 18:41.722
Will it work?

18:43.657 --> 18:45.826
Can we make her more calm?

18:45.926 --> 18:47.160
Undoubtedly.

18:48.429 --> 18:50.797
Can we render the beast dormant?

18:52.165 --> 18:53.299
It's possible.

18:54.701 --> 18:56.537
But can we make her love you?

18:58.505 --> 18:59.773
I want her back.

19:02.008 --> 19:03.209
As she was.

19:06.747 --> 19:08.849
But before I bring her to this place...

19:11.818 --> 19:13.587
show me what you can do.

19:21.795 --> 19:25.432
VANESSA: ...and without my
God I feel utterly alone.

19:27.768 --> 19:29.836
I don't even know who I am meant to be.

19:32.372 --> 19:33.607
(VANESSA SNIFFLES)

19:36.910 --> 19:38.244
(SOBBING)

19:42.483 --> 19:43.750
(RECORDING CYLINDER STOPS)

19:44.785 --> 19:46.620
(PANTING)

19:56.630 --> 19:57.864
(SNIFFLES)

20:17.651 --> 20:19.252
Filthy habit.

20:19.352 --> 20:20.921
I've been trying to quit.

20:22.689 --> 20:24.057
- (KNOCKING ON DOOR)
- Yes?

20:25.859 --> 20:27.393
Yes, Mr. Renfield?

20:28.929 --> 20:30.997
Oh, your next appointment
has been waiting.

20:31.732 --> 20:33.233
In a moment.

20:37.037 --> 20:38.238
(DOOR CLOSES)

20:45.145 --> 20:46.713
Look at me, Miss Ives.

20:50.216 --> 20:52.218
We will find our way through this.

20:56.457 --> 20:58.559
But today, right now,

20:58.659 --> 20:59.926
I want you to do something

21:00.026 --> 21:02.195
that you believe might make you happy.

21:02.295 --> 21:03.697
Even for a moment.

21:04.531 --> 21:06.066
Doesn't matter what it is,

21:06.166 --> 21:08.735
no matter how capricious or unlikely.

21:08.835 --> 21:10.771
Tell me about it at our next session.

21:13.940 --> 21:15.976
That'll be all. Good day.

21:29.122 --> 21:30.090
(DOOR CLOSES)

21:30.190 --> 21:31.525
(SIGHS)

21:46.139 --> 21:47.708
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

22:27.581 --> 22:29.015
- (TYPEWRITER CLACKING)
- SIR MALCOLM: <i>Cable October,</i>

22:29.115 --> 22:31.685
<i>date uncertain, 1892.</i>

22:32.553 --> 22:33.520
<i>Vanessa.</i>

22:33.620 --> 22:36.557
<i>Traveling now. Bound for the Americas.</i>

22:36.657 --> 22:39.159
<i>Have in mind to do some hunting.</i>

22:39.259 --> 22:40.427
<i>Tell me you are well.</i>

22:40.527 --> 22:41.562
(GROANING)

22:41.662 --> 22:42.963
<i>Signed, Malcolm Murray.</i>

22:43.063 --> 22:45.599
God grant us anything but ships.

22:46.567 --> 22:48.735
You've been in many,
though, in your travels.

22:48.835 --> 22:50.637
Doesn't make it any more pleasant.

22:52.506 --> 22:54.107
I was once of a mind to
travel to South America

22:54.207 --> 22:55.241
to hunt the big cats.

22:55.341 --> 22:57.578
But the prospect of the ocean...

22:57.678 --> 22:59.079
brought me to my senses.

22:59.179 --> 23:00.781
KAETENAY: Which cats?

23:00.881 --> 23:02.483
SIR MALCOLM: Oh, jaguars and the like.

23:02.583 --> 23:05.118
Lions in Africa are easy
prey for the most part,

23:05.218 --> 23:06.520
especially if they've fed.

23:06.620 --> 23:09.222
Rhinos can be challenging.

23:09.322 --> 23:11.525
You speak for your race.

23:12.859 --> 23:14.828
Nature is to be hunted.

23:15.361 --> 23:16.863
Your people hunt.

23:17.664 --> 23:18.732
Yes.

23:20.133 --> 23:21.435
And our quarry now?

23:21.535 --> 23:24.505
Hunting a man is no great thing.

23:24.605 --> 23:26.640
They are slow and predictable.

23:26.740 --> 23:27.941
They can be found always

23:28.041 --> 23:30.176
where their appetites lead them...

23:30.276 --> 23:32.479
To eat, to sleep, to fuck.

23:32.579 --> 23:34.147
Man is no great thing.

23:34.247 --> 23:36.049
And Mr. Chandler?

23:36.149 --> 23:37.383
Or Talbot, as you'd call him?

23:37.484 --> 23:40.053
His appetites lead him elsewhere.

23:40.153 --> 23:42.122
Where? Night.

23:43.890 --> 23:46.527
Do all your people speak
so enigmatically?

23:47.561 --> 23:48.695
Yes.

23:52.966 --> 23:56.302
Ethan came to me with blood on his face.

23:56.403 --> 24:00.006
The blood of my brothers
and sisters and children.

24:00.106 --> 24:01.608
He wanted to die.

24:01.708 --> 24:03.877
He wanted me to take his scalp

24:03.977 --> 24:06.146
and wear it on my belt.

24:07.313 --> 24:08.314
And why didn't you?

24:08.415 --> 24:11.418
I thought it crueler to let him live.

24:11.518 --> 24:13.754
Have you ever hated a man so much

24:13.854 --> 24:16.256
you wanted him to suffer alongside you

24:16.356 --> 24:18.024
for all your days?

24:19.159 --> 24:21.528
So you could watch it.

24:21.628 --> 24:24.197
Such was your anger
from what they had done

24:24.297 --> 24:25.999
to you and your family.

24:26.099 --> 24:27.333
Yes.

24:29.335 --> 24:30.671
A woman.

24:31.004 --> 24:33.407
What happened between
you and this woman?

24:34.541 --> 24:37.811
In time, we stopped wounding each other.

24:39.079 --> 24:42.382
The anger became something else,

24:42.483 --> 24:44.084
equally powerful.

24:45.051 --> 24:46.019
Love.

24:46.119 --> 24:47.387
Of a kind.

24:47.488 --> 24:48.589
Like a daughter?

24:49.222 --> 24:50.691
Of a kind.

24:50.791 --> 24:52.526
Then you understand.

24:55.228 --> 24:57.330
Let us speak to our son.

25:21.387 --> 25:23.824
(CHANTING IN NATIVE LANGUAGE)

25:28.562 --> 25:31.565
(CONTINUES CHANTING IN NATIVE LANGUAGE)

25:44.110 --> 25:45.311
(GASPS)

25:45.946 --> 25:47.814
(CHANTING CONTINUES)

26:17.377 --> 26:18.912
- KAETENAY: My son...
- (GASPS)

26:23.617 --> 26:25.018
(GRUNTING)

26:28.054 --> 26:29.456
Look into my eyes.

26:30.957 --> 26:33.093
Did they look at you
when you killed them?

26:34.127 --> 26:35.128
Yes.

26:36.329 --> 26:38.031
Come near me in life, old man,

26:38.131 --> 26:40.434
and I will take your hair
and wear it on my belt.

26:40.534 --> 26:42.569
That's a cheap Comanche trick.

26:42.669 --> 26:44.405
Good to frighten whites,

26:44.505 --> 26:46.072
but wasted effort for an Apache.

26:46.172 --> 26:47.207
I'm not an Apache!

26:47.377 --> 26:49.179
_

26:49.204 --> 26:50.995
_

26:51.088 --> 26:53.158
_

27:01.221 --> 27:03.356
Where are you now, Ethan?

27:03.457 --> 27:04.891
Outside of Cascabel.

27:06.159 --> 27:08.194
They're taking me home to see my father.

27:09.162 --> 27:10.363
And then?

27:11.331 --> 27:12.799
I'll end it with him.

27:13.500 --> 27:15.536
Just as one day I'll end it with you.

27:17.904 --> 27:20.574
Keep an ocean between us, old man.

27:21.742 --> 27:23.343
I'll see you presently, my son.

27:23.444 --> 27:24.678
Don't!

27:26.312 --> 27:27.781
I'm not the man you knew.

27:29.983 --> 27:31.351
There's blood on my teeth

27:32.953 --> 27:34.421
and in my soul, I think.

27:37.157 --> 27:39.693
Then you are the Apache I need.

27:39.793 --> 27:41.294
(GASPS)

28:03.149 --> 28:04.718
He knows we come.

28:15.496 --> 28:17.598
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

28:32.312 --> 28:33.780
DR. SWEET: ...ranging
from the least weasel,

28:33.880 --> 28:34.881
<i>Mustela nivalis,</i>

28:34.981 --> 28:37.918
to the polar bear, <i>Ursus maritimus.</i>

28:38.018 --> 28:39.953
Unlike many of the other mammalians,

28:40.053 --> 28:41.422
and rather remarkably,

28:41.522 --> 28:44.224
members of the <i>vulpes</i> genre
are found on every continent,

28:44.324 --> 28:45.626
save for Antarctica.

28:45.726 --> 28:48.228
Nor is this to say that the
widespread distribution

28:48.328 --> 28:49.730
of the common red fox,

28:49.830 --> 28:50.797
<i>Vulpes vulpes,</i>

28:50.897 --> 28:53.434
with its many sub-genera,
is meant to suggest

28:53.534 --> 28:55.602
a commonality with the household dog,

28:55.702 --> 28:57.771
<i>Canis lupus familiaris,</i>

28:57.871 --> 28:59.840
though there are marked similarities

28:59.940 --> 29:03.510
within the taxonomy of both animals.

29:08.314 --> 29:09.816
Which brings us, in the typically

29:09.916 --> 29:11.351
roundabout way of nature,

29:11.452 --> 29:12.719
to the arachnids.

29:12.819 --> 29:14.187
Take, for example,

29:14.287 --> 29:16.623
the modest desert scorpion.

29:16.723 --> 29:19.560
Now, can any of you tell me about, say,

29:19.660 --> 29:21.361
the Omdurman scorpion?

29:22.896 --> 29:24.330
(GASPS) Miss?

29:25.466 --> 29:28.669
Do you mean the "Deathstalker"
scorpion, Dr. Sweet?

29:28.769 --> 29:30.604
Why, yes, Miss, I do.

29:30.704 --> 29:32.305
Those found in the Sudan, for example?

29:32.406 --> 29:34.340
Yes, precisely those.

29:34.441 --> 29:38.979
Now, can any of you tell me
which are the most dangerous?

29:44.451 --> 29:45.419
Yes, Miss?

29:45.519 --> 29:47.421
I understand the smaller varieties

29:47.521 --> 29:49.189
are particularly venomous.

29:49.289 --> 29:50.657
Wouldn't expect that, would you?

29:50.757 --> 29:52.325
I would actually.

29:52.426 --> 29:55.596
Not to mention, well, the albinos.

30:01.602 --> 30:04.405
They're beyond tiresome,
but I have to do them,

30:04.505 --> 30:05.739
the lectures.

30:05.839 --> 30:07.841
The burden of command.

30:07.941 --> 30:10.944
Public subscription pays for a
fair number of my beasties.

30:11.044 --> 30:13.447
Not to mention, the expeditions.

30:13.547 --> 30:16.016
- Expeditions?
- Yes.

30:16.116 --> 30:19.319
We don't just sit in London
and stuff the odd animal.

30:19.420 --> 30:22.322
We sponsor expeditions
all over the globe.

30:22.423 --> 30:23.724
Where have you been?

30:24.591 --> 30:26.226
Oh, I don't go.

30:27.293 --> 30:30.431
(CHUCKLING) Not made for
adventuring myself.

30:30.531 --> 30:31.998
I hoped I would when I was younger,

30:32.098 --> 30:33.967
being cursed with Jules Verne.

30:34.067 --> 30:36.403
Read <i>20,000 Leagues Under
the Sea</i> when I was a boy

30:36.503 --> 30:38.905
and it gave me such a
passion to see the world.

30:39.005 --> 30:40.674
Live like Captain Nemo,

30:40.774 --> 30:43.176
with that swagger and freedom.
(CHUCKLES)

30:44.177 --> 30:45.412
But...

30:46.179 --> 30:47.280
But?

30:48.248 --> 30:50.784
We're not made of such stuff
as our heroes, are we?

30:52.052 --> 30:53.954
I suppose not.

30:54.054 --> 30:55.622
Sad, really.

30:55.722 --> 30:56.823
But...

30:56.923 --> 30:59.760
if we can't walk with them,
we can always follow.

31:01.227 --> 31:03.664
And yours? Heroes, that is?

31:05.866 --> 31:07.601
Joan of Arc. Ah.

31:09.770 --> 31:12.906
I met her in the Shakespeare
as that hellcat of Orleans.

31:13.006 --> 31:16.209
Then I read the Schiller and...

31:16.309 --> 31:18.211
learned of her mighty passion.

31:18.912 --> 31:20.847
Dying for her beliefs and her God,

31:20.947 --> 31:22.649
true to herself no matter the darkness

31:22.749 --> 31:24.250
that gathered 'round her.

31:25.285 --> 31:27.888
It's said she sang on
the pyre as she died.

31:27.988 --> 31:29.389
A tragic end.

31:30.290 --> 31:31.792
I don't think so.

31:31.892 --> 31:34.027
She heard a voice and believed it.

31:34.127 --> 31:36.196
To have belief in anything
with such confidence

31:36.296 --> 31:37.498
is heroic.

31:38.231 --> 31:41.234
Perhaps if I had more I would
have traveled with Nemo.

31:41.334 --> 31:42.436
What happened to him in the book?

31:42.536 --> 31:43.804
I don't remember.

31:43.904 --> 31:46.206
He was in a number of
the books, actually.

31:46.306 --> 31:48.742
Story has it he died of old age

31:48.842 --> 31:51.845
somewhere in a forgotten
grotto in the South Pacific.

31:52.145 --> 31:53.614
But I don't believe it.

31:53.714 --> 31:54.948
I think he's still out there.

31:55.048 --> 31:56.550
(SOFTLY) Waiting for you.

32:00.787 --> 32:02.456
I'm glad you came today.

32:02.556 --> 32:04.491
I hope my lecture
didn't bore you unduly.

32:05.225 --> 32:06.460
Not at all.

32:06.560 --> 32:07.861
I give them every Wednesday.

32:07.961 --> 32:10.831
Next week, the thrilling tale
of the Madagascan lemur.

32:10.931 --> 32:12.433
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

32:12.533 --> 32:13.934
Good day to you, Miss...

32:15.268 --> 32:17.337
Vanessa Ives. Miss Ives. Yes.

32:18.071 --> 32:19.540
(CHUCKLING) Good day, good...

32:19.640 --> 32:20.641
good day.

32:53.740 --> 32:55.476
(BELL TOLLING)

33:10.557 --> 33:12.258
(FAINT MUSIC PLAYING)

33:27.273 --> 33:28.909
(BALLROOM MUSIC PLAYING ON PHONOGRAPH)

33:31.978 --> 33:33.514
(CHUCKLING)

34:01.842 --> 34:02.843
Oh, you're up.

34:05.412 --> 34:06.713
Wonderful.

34:14.286 --> 34:15.522
(MUSIC STOPS)

34:24.397 --> 34:26.800
We thought it best to let you sleep.

34:29.268 --> 34:30.704
You must be hungry.

34:31.638 --> 34:32.973
- Please sit down.
- No.

34:35.576 --> 34:36.810
I'll stand.

34:38.745 --> 34:40.414
Welcome to your new home,

34:41.882 --> 34:43.949
if you'll do us that courtesy.

34:45.284 --> 34:46.252
You killed them.

34:46.351 --> 34:47.387
And would have killed more.

34:47.487 --> 34:48.489
And shall.

34:52.426 --> 34:53.494
Why?

34:58.699 --> 35:00.100
This room.

35:03.437 --> 35:05.005
The opulence dazzles you.

35:05.939 --> 35:07.574
As it did me when I stood there...

35:09.342 --> 35:13.079
A feral animal raised on the streets,

35:15.315 --> 35:18.018
forced to my knees when I was a girl,

35:18.852 --> 35:22.355
servicing any man with two bob

35:23.089 --> 35:25.225
and a hard back to his hand.

35:28.228 --> 35:31.197
And there I would have stayed
and there I would have died...

35:31.297 --> 35:32.633
(SHUDDERS)

35:32.733 --> 35:35.368
but for a strange working of fate

35:36.703 --> 35:38.439
that allowed me a new life.

35:42.208 --> 35:43.610
Will you do the same?

35:45.846 --> 35:47.080
Yes.

35:48.148 --> 35:50.451
DORIAN: No matter the cost?
Beggar the cost.

35:55.589 --> 35:57.190
And the men from your past?

36:00.594 --> 36:02.596
The ones who used you.

36:03.530 --> 36:04.831
The monsters.

36:04.931 --> 36:06.700
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

36:09.536 --> 36:11.405
Will you forgive them?

36:13.407 --> 36:15.241
Would you have me forgive them?

36:17.811 --> 36:19.245
No, no.

36:20.414 --> 36:21.748
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

36:23.183 --> 36:25.185
We shall have, my dear,

36:27.554 --> 36:30.457
a monumental revenge.

36:48.509 --> 36:51.111
(SCREAMING) Leave me!

36:51.211 --> 36:52.679
(SCREAMING SAVAGELY)

36:56.249 --> 36:57.951
(STRAINING)

37:05.859 --> 37:06.927
How long do you want him?

37:07.027 --> 37:08.061
DR. JEKYLL: I'll alert
you when I'm done.

37:08.161 --> 37:09.129
As you like.

37:09.229 --> 37:11.231
As you like, "Doctor."

37:12.032 --> 37:13.767
Yeah. That's what I meant.

37:13.867 --> 37:15.569
DR. JEKYLL: A Scotsman, this one.

37:15.669 --> 37:17.103
He made a half-hearted attempt

37:17.203 --> 37:18.805
to assassinate Her
Majesty at Balmoral...

37:18.905 --> 37:20.306
Ranting about Scottish independence

37:20.407 --> 37:22.976
and the Bonnie Prince and the 45.

37:23.076 --> 37:24.545
More of a failed social agitator

37:24.645 --> 37:26.012
than a lunatic, actually.

37:26.880 --> 37:28.114
But this place soon took care of that.

37:28.214 --> 37:29.916
Can you get ready with
a syringe, Victor?

37:33.520 --> 37:35.856
All the hopeful regicides end up here.

37:35.956 --> 37:37.458
Poor bastards.

37:37.558 --> 37:39.259
- (SCREAMING)
- Whatever you do, old man,

37:39.359 --> 37:40.861
don't threaten the Queen.

37:40.961 --> 37:42.262
Tell me what you see.

37:42.362 --> 37:43.597
Be specific.

37:43.697 --> 37:44.998
(PANTING)

37:45.098 --> 37:46.500
Dilated pupils...

37:47.901 --> 37:49.403
- erratic ocular focus...
- (GROANING)

37:50.370 --> 37:52.105
broken capillaries throughout.

37:53.640 --> 37:55.809
Eczema on the scalp and skin,

37:55.909 --> 37:58.745
jaundice, poor nutrition.

37:58.845 --> 38:01.114
Teeth are decaying,

38:01.214 --> 38:03.316
indications of incipient scurvy.

38:04.618 --> 38:06.920
- Pulse is...
- (GROANING)

38:08.589 --> 38:10.424
- extremely elevated...
- (GROWLS)

38:10.524 --> 38:12.426
- And highly agitated.
- (GROWLS)

38:15.195 --> 38:16.997
A monster, would you say?

38:18.999 --> 38:20.767
I've seen monsters.

38:20.867 --> 38:22.503
Well, violently deranged at least?

38:22.603 --> 38:24.438
(SCREAMING)

38:24.538 --> 38:25.772
Yes.

38:27.073 --> 38:30.577
So, let us see what
miracles we can work.

38:31.177 --> 38:32.413
(CHOKING)

38:36.983 --> 38:38.519
(WHIMPERING)

38:44.124 --> 38:45.859
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

38:58.439 --> 38:59.573
(GASPING)

39:00.240 --> 39:01.608
(SCREAMING MANIACALLY)

39:19.826 --> 39:21.194
Mr. Balfour.

39:21.962 --> 39:23.964
Will you not greet our guest?

39:31.772 --> 39:33.574
I could do with some water, sir...

39:34.374 --> 39:36.042
if you're so inclined.

39:44.818 --> 39:47.287
Honestly, no.

39:47.721 --> 39:50.290
It doesn't have the spark of life.

39:50.390 --> 39:52.693
Needs more shine to the eyes. That's it.

39:52.793 --> 39:55.696
More sense of nocturnal danger, I think.

39:55.796 --> 39:57.964
- Afternoon post, sir.
- Ah, thank you.

39:58.765 --> 40:00.667
Keep at it, Phillip.

40:00.767 --> 40:02.636
Nocturnal danger, yes?

40:06.673 --> 40:08.409
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

40:21.922 --> 40:23.790
VANESSA: <i>Dear Dr. Sweet.</i>

40:23.890 --> 40:25.926
<i>If you're in mind to have an adventure,</i>

40:26.026 --> 40:30.130
please meet me at the address
<i>noted below at 7:45 tonight.</i>

40:30.230 --> 40:32.933
<i>Sincerely, the woman
you always forget...</i>

40:33.033 --> 40:34.034
(CHUCKLES)

40:34.134 --> 40:35.969
...who is called Vanessa Ives.

40:39.473 --> 40:40.674
(MUSIC PLAYING)

40:46.480 --> 40:47.948
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

40:58.425 --> 41:00.293
How did you know?

41:00.393 --> 41:02.228
I saw an advertisement in the paper.

41:03.129 --> 41:05.899
I don't know that I've ever
been asked out by a woman.

41:05.999 --> 41:07.000
(CHUCKLES)

41:07.100 --> 41:09.035
Boldness is, alas, part of my nature.

41:09.836 --> 41:11.304
The best part I'm sure.

41:12.839 --> 41:14.307
(APPLAUSE AND CHEERING)

41:19.012 --> 41:20.113
Ladies and gentlemen...

41:20.213 --> 41:24.451
journey with us now across
endless fathoms of wonder.

41:24.551 --> 41:26.487
Join Captain Nemo

41:26.587 --> 41:29.956
on his bold expeditions as he travels...

41:30.056 --> 41:33.660
20,000 leagues under the sea!

41:33.760 --> 41:35.596
(PEOPLE GASP AND APPLAUD)

41:40.100 --> 41:41.201
(PEOPLE GASPING)

41:51.812 --> 41:53.013
(GASPS)

41:56.983 --> 41:58.652
(GASPING AND APPLAUDING)

42:06.359 --> 42:07.594
(ALL GASP)

42:21.041 --> 42:22.275
DR. SEWARD: <i>Have you sinned?</i>

42:22.375 --> 42:23.877
VANESSA: <i>Everyone has sinned.</i>

42:23.977 --> 42:25.278
- DR. SEWARD: <i>Have they?</i>
- VANESSA: <i>Mmm-hmm.</i>

42:25.378 --> 42:27.180
- DR. SEWARD: <i>Including you?</i>
- VANESSA: <i>Yes.</i>

42:27.280 --> 42:29.483
- DR. SEWARD: <i>When?</i>
- (VANESSA SCOFFS)

42:29.583 --> 42:31.585
VANESSA: <i>How long is your cylinder?</i>

42:31.685 --> 42:33.720
DR. SEWARD: <i>Start with the first time.</i>

42:33.820 --> 42:37.123
(VANESSA SIGHS) <i>Apart from
childhood indiscretions,</i>

42:38.124 --> 42:40.727
<i>the first of importance then.</i>

42:40.827 --> 42:42.529
<i>I betrayed my dearest friend Mina</i>

42:42.629 --> 42:44.698
<i>- on the eve of her wedding.</i>
- DR. SEWARD: <i>How?</i>

42:45.966 --> 42:47.000
<i>How?</i>

42:47.100 --> 42:48.802
VANESSA: <i>I seduced her fiance.</i>

42:49.770 --> 42:51.337
DR. SEWARD: <i>What was the result?</i>

42:51.438 --> 42:53.006
VANESSA: <i>It led to catastrophe.</i>

42:53.106 --> 42:55.275
<i>-And eventually her death.</i>
- (CHUCKLING)

43:04.585 --> 43:06.052
Can't sell you what I don't have.

43:06.152 --> 43:07.988
Well's all but dry.

43:08.088 --> 43:09.923
I've got six men, six horses.

43:10.023 --> 43:12.993
That's a couple, three gallons
each man, more for the horses.

43:13.727 --> 43:15.195
Call it two score gallons, worst case.

43:15.295 --> 43:16.763
(PROPRIETOR) You go look at that well.

43:16.863 --> 43:17.998
It's mud pretty much.

43:18.965 --> 43:20.434
Like I say, there ain't no water

43:20.534 --> 43:22.168
between here and Hell and back.

43:22.268 --> 43:23.737
(SIGHS)

43:30.310 --> 43:32.112
You look sad.

43:34.881 --> 43:36.282
What did you do?

43:37.183 --> 43:38.785
I killed a senator's son.

43:39.753 --> 43:42.288
(SCOFFS) Serves you right then.

43:43.790 --> 43:45.291
They gonna hang you?

43:46.793 --> 43:47.928
Not exactly.

43:48.028 --> 43:50.330
You come to a bad end anyway, yeah?

43:51.197 --> 43:52.666
Of that I have no doubt.

43:55.335 --> 43:57.170
_

44:00.163 --> 44:02.421
_

44:09.783 --> 44:14.421
_

44:14.755 --> 44:16.056
_

44:16.913 --> 44:22.077
_

44:22.741 --> 44:24.749
_

44:25.031 --> 44:26.567
_

44:26.960 --> 44:31.335
_

44:31.360 --> 44:33.280
_

44:33.624 --> 44:35.569
_

44:36.796 --> 44:39.702
_

44:40.655 --> 44:42.585
_

44:44.007 --> 44:45.820
_

44:46.520 --> 44:49.355
(IN ENGLISH) I would
help you if I could.

44:52.459 --> 44:55.996
What you can do for me is
leave this room right now.

44:56.096 --> 44:57.564
You understand?

44:58.965 --> 45:00.100
Bless you, son.

45:01.568 --> 45:02.936
Thank you, Mother.

45:19.352 --> 45:20.587
(EXHALES)

45:20.687 --> 45:22.656
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

45:38.238 --> 45:40.240
(BONES SHIFTING)

45:41.442 --> 45:42.509
(GROWLING)

45:43.844 --> 45:45.178
(GROANS)

45:47.481 --> 45:48.682
(CONTINUES GROWLING)

45:54.988 --> 45:56.322
(SCREAMS)

45:56.423 --> 45:57.691
MAN: What the...

46:00.360 --> 46:02.228
(GROWLS SOFTLY)

46:02.328 --> 46:04.330
(GASPING)

46:04.431 --> 46:06.266
(GROWLING)

46:12.773 --> 46:14.074
(ETHAN SNARLING)

46:21.882 --> 46:23.484
How I've missed you.

46:24.985 --> 46:27.353
- (HORSE NEIGHS)
- (INDISTINCT CHATTER)

46:29.022 --> 46:30.491
VANESSA: I've always loved the ocean

46:30.591 --> 46:33.427
and felt great affection
for creatures of the deep.

46:33.527 --> 46:34.928
I suppose it goes without saying that

46:35.028 --> 46:37.464
they don't actually get so big,

46:37.564 --> 46:38.665
squids, I mean.

46:38.765 --> 46:41.001
Cephalopods are delicate
little things, in fact.

46:41.768 --> 46:42.869
(CHUCKLES)

46:45.105 --> 46:47.841
Well, do you favor some coffee?

46:48.875 --> 46:50.611
Simpson's is open, I think.

46:51.678 --> 46:53.780
Perhaps another time.

46:55.449 --> 46:56.783
I'm sorry.

46:58.685 --> 46:59.986
Of course.

47:01.154 --> 47:02.756
May I get you a cab?

47:03.356 --> 47:04.825
I'll be fine, thank you.

47:07.160 --> 47:09.162
Thank you for tonight.

47:09.262 --> 47:11.432
It's meant more to me than I can say

47:11.532 --> 47:13.534
and I do look forward to the next time.

47:14.234 --> 47:15.936
The Madagascan lemur.

47:23.677 --> 47:25.812
I'll never forget your name again.

48:06.887 --> 48:09.089
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

48:48.895 --> 48:49.896
(DOOR OPENS)

49:08.615 --> 49:10.216
You mustn't be here.

49:10.851 --> 49:12.786
There's nothing here for you.

49:12.886 --> 49:14.387
(LILY SIGHS)

49:14.488 --> 49:16.056
Where you go, I belong.

49:17.991 --> 49:20.427
God help you if you
follow my path, Victor.

49:23.163 --> 49:24.598
(INHALES)

49:24.698 --> 49:26.366
Take your romance

49:27.768 --> 49:29.302
and your memories,

49:29.402 --> 49:31.371
which are a most kind fiction, and go.

49:31.472 --> 49:32.739
FRANKENSTEIN: No.

49:36.543 --> 49:38.912
I must save you from all of this,

49:39.780 --> 49:42.082
one way or another.

49:42.182 --> 49:44.217
You're my responsibility.

49:44.317 --> 49:45.351
I created you.

49:45.452 --> 49:47.788
I need no man to save me.

49:50.924 --> 49:52.158
And I think,

49:53.994 --> 49:55.128
in a way,

49:56.963 --> 49:59.399
I created you more than you created me.

50:11.277 --> 50:13.079
First love, Victor.

50:14.648 --> 50:16.417
You will recover.

50:17.383 --> 50:19.252
Please don't come here again.

50:19.686 --> 50:22.456
You will not like what I am becoming.

50:32.165 --> 50:33.467
(SOBBING)

50:58.224 --> 50:59.860
VANESSA: <i>Dear Sir Malcolm,</i>

50:59.960 --> 51:02.696
<i>I read your last cable
with great interest.</i>

51:02.796 --> 51:04.965
<i>You certainly are traveling far afield.</i>

51:05.866 --> 51:08.368
<i>You say you're heading to the Americas.</i>

51:08.469 --> 51:10.704
<i>I wonder if you're going
to the United States,</i>

51:10.804 --> 51:13.039
<i>and what you might be hunting there.</i>

51:13.139 --> 51:15.141
<i>Perhaps you'll visit the West</i>

51:15.241 --> 51:19.646
<i>and walk the roads of our
lost friend, Mr. Chandler.</i>

51:21.782 --> 51:24.918
<i>Did you know American
coyotes mate for life?</i>

51:25.018 --> 51:26.787
<i>And that there are certain octopi</i>

51:26.887 --> 51:29.022
<i>who can manipulate their
bodies through holes</i>

51:29.122 --> 51:31.425
<i>no larger than a ha'penny coin?</i>

51:32.559 --> 51:34.394
<i>As you can tell, I've
developed an interest</i>

51:34.495 --> 51:36.196
<i>in zoology of late.</i>

51:38.364 --> 51:39.633
(GENTLE THUDDING)

51:39.733 --> 51:40.834
<i>I miss you.</i>

51:41.401 --> 51:43.303
<i>But please know that I am well</i>

51:43.404 --> 51:45.939
<i>and abide in something like contentment.</i>

51:46.039 --> 51:47.207
(VIOLIN PLAYING)

51:47.307 --> 51:48.975
<i>In fact, it's all rather boring here.</i>

51:49.075 --> 51:50.076
(MOUSE SQUEAKS)

51:53.279 --> 51:56.382
<i>As ever, with love, Vanessa.</i>

51:58.752 --> 52:00.320
(MAN BREATHES HEAVILY)

52:04.425 --> 52:05.826
(BELL RINGS IN THE DISTANCE)

52:10.631 --> 52:12.666
(VIOLIN CONTINUES PLAYING)

52:18.539 --> 52:20.641
(THE MASTER WHISPERS)
She has told her story.

52:20.741 --> 52:23.143
(WHIMPERING) Yes, Master.

52:24.478 --> 52:26.379
THE MASTER: Did the doctor believe it?

52:26.480 --> 52:28.048
I don't think so.

52:28.148 --> 52:29.783
(VIOLIN CONTINUES PLAYING)

52:31.084 --> 52:33.487
Give me blood. Please.

52:37.123 --> 52:38.492
Please!

52:40.193 --> 52:41.194
(LOW RUMBLING)

52:43.664 --> 52:45.632
Kneel, child.

52:50.236 --> 52:53.206
You will be flesh of my flesh...

52:53.306 --> 52:54.941
(SLURPING)

52:57.377 --> 53:00.146
Blood of my blood.

